### 🛠️ Key Improvements Implemented

1. **Focus Trapping & Restoration (Manual Intake Modal)**:
   - Programmatically shifts focus to the first text input (`#form-title`) when the intake modal is opened.
   - Captures `Tab`/`Shift+Tab` keyboard inputs to loop focus between interactive modal elements.
   - Restores focus back to the button that triggered the modal upon closure.

2. **Contrast Enhancement (WCAG 2.1 AA Compliant)**:
   - Modified CSS variables for `success`, `warning`, `error`, and `info` badges in [global.css](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-ui-accessibility/apps/web/app/global.css) for better readability.
   - Updated primary action button backgrounds (e.g., Approve changed to emerald-800 (`#065f46`) and Danger/Reject changed to red-700 (`#b91c1c`)) to exceed the minimum `4.5:1` contrast ratio.
   - Implemented high-contrast alert boxes for error displays.

3. **Motion Reductions & Smooth Scroll Prefs**:
   - Integrated media queries in CSS to turn off loading spinners and pulse transitions when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` is detected.
   - Configured `scrollToEvidence` to use instant scroll (`behavior: "auto"`) and skip highlighted fade-outs when reduced motion is preferred.

4. **Failure State Error Banners**:
   - Added state hooks for fetching failures (`hypothesesError`, `plansError`, `patchesError`, and `approvalsError`).
   - Replaced silent page empties with explicit `role="alert"` boxes using a high-contrast dark scheme (`#1e131d` background, `#fca5a5` text).

5. **Responsive Layouts**:
   - Stacks modal sections vertically on mobile screens.
   - Fixed missing `grid` class inside the incident room layout container to align columns on desktop viewports and cleanly stack them on mobile devices.

6. **Automated E2E Verification**:
   - Created [accessibility.spec.ts](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-ui-accessibility/apps/web/e2e/accessibility.spec.ts) running automated Axe audits and verifying keyboard navigation/mobile viewports.

